% if: executable(poetry)

Poetry - Version Constraints

Manage dependencies in your Python project with [prgm]poetry[/prgm]. Use version constraints to limit the range of one-or-more dependencies.

Adding dependencies with version constraints

$ [prgm]poetry add[/prgm] [arg-value]package[/arg-value]@[arg-value]^2.0[/arg-value]       # Add with version constraint
$ [prgm]poetry add[/prgm] [arg-value]package[/arg-value]@[arg-value]latest[/arg-value]    # Add latest version

Version constraints:

  [cyan]^2.0[/cyan]        Compatible    [magenta](>=2.0.0, <3.0.0)[/magenta]
  [cyan]~2.1[/cyan]        Approximately [magenta](>=2.1.0, <2.2.0)[/magenta]
  [cyan]>=2.0,<3.0[/cyan]  Range
  [cyan]2.1.3[/cyan]       Exact version
